Virtual Functions can be inline ?

Inline Functions  - 
Inline functions are used to replace function call with function definition.
It is used for faster execution of program.

They are used for efficiency.
Inline functions substitutes whole Function definition at the time of function call.

 By default all member functions can be consider as Inline except Virtual.


Can virtual functions be inline ?

If virtual functions called with base class reference or pointer then it can not be inline because functions call get resolved at run time.

If virtual functions call with that particular class reference then function call resolved at compile time that time we can keep virtual functions inline.
